Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Remove dough from can; do not unroll. Cut rolled dough into 12 (1/2-inch) slices. Place on sprayed cookie sheet. Brush top of each slice with butter. Sprinkle each with 1 teaspoon blue cheese and 1 teaspoon pecans. Bake at 375 degrees F for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Meanwhile, in small bowl, combine sauce ingredients; mix well. Arrange spirals on serving platter. Top each with about 1 teaspoon sauce. Garnish with blue cheese.